&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;THIS POST IS FIXED TERM/SECONDMENT FOR 12 MONTHS DUE TO MATERNITY COVER &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a fixed term or secondment opportunity to cover maternity leave to meet the needs of the service. If you are interested in a secondment position please gain permission from your line manager before applying.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for an experienced part-time administrator to support the Occupational Therapy service within the Division of Mental Health and Learning Disabilities for 22.5 hours per week to cover a period of maternity leave. We are looking for a friendly, enthusiastic, organised and productive individual to support the service as a central administrator based at St Cadoc&#39;s hospital. Some duties will take place in other parts of the health board across Gwent as needed to support the service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;22.5 hours per week- core hours to be worked from Monday to Friday between 8.30 am to 5pm and candidates must be flexible to meet the needs of the service. Possibility to work some hours from home once the role is established. The successful candidate will have a keen eye for detail, a professional manner, excellent communication and organisation skills and the ability to work autonomously using own initiative.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Experience in a similar role using various systems is essential (e.g. ESR, TRAC, Oracle etc).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post; Welsh and/or English speakers are equally welcome to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing date: 11th November 2020.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Amy Mitchell&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Divisional head of Occupational therapy- Mental health and learning disabilities division&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;07930691314&lt;/p&gt;
